{
 "name": "RPlog_To_Kill_A_Karrde_Part_2",
 "title": "To Kill a Karrde, Part 2: The Cage Aboard the Trader's Triumph",
 "summary": "Aboard the Black Sun courier Trader's Triumph, the newly promoted Otactre Tyy'sun Eson holds a captive Talon Karrde, the famed smuggler chief, in a cage after a bloody ambush on Nar Shaddaa left both men wounded. Eson, driven by rage and a hatred born of his brutal past, demands details of Karrde's Outer Rim operations while his Vigo, Lyle Derfill, urges caution against drawing galactic attention. Karrde plays for time, baiting Eson's pride and offering a deal, then makes a desperate physical lunge that briefly bowls the Twi'lek over before a stun bolt and Eson's superior ferocity put him down. As Eson prepares to execute his enemy, an unexpected transmission from Ryloth bearing the name Sarhavian Eson stays his hand. He orders Karrde bound and taken to a planetside compound for interrogation before execution, and the smuggler chief slips back into darkness.",
